Description: Fate Averruncus gives Negi a choice: fight him and save the world or flee and guarantee his student’s safety.
Title: NEGIMA! (MAGISTER NEGI MAGI), VOL. 25
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: Naurto learns more secrets from his past and moves closer to discovering the identity of his nemesis, Pain.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 47
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: Maka, an arms expert, wants to turn the Soul Eater, her living scythe, into the ultimate weapon for Death.
Title: SOUL EATER, VOL. 2
Author: Atsushi Ohkubo

Description: Cross Academy has day and evening students, but the latter have a secret: they are vampires.
Title: VAMPIRE KNIGHT, VOL. 9
Author: Matsuri Hino

Description: Sebastian is a loyal butler who moves easily from dinner parties to the underworld. Is he too good to be true? Is he even human?
Title: BLACK BUTLER, VOL. 1
Author: Yana Toboso

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy. How will she survive the pursuit of demons who want the power in her blood?
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 3
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji

Description:
Alice wanders into a very different part of Wonderland in this interpretation of the classic tale. 

In this new area of the fantasy land, every man is in love with Alice... and firearms.
Title: ALICE IN THE COUNTRY OF HEARTS: THE CLOCKMAKER'S STORY
Author: Quinrose and Soumei Hoshino

Description: When the follower of an old enemy returns to take revenge, Yugi Mutou must duel to save a friend’s life.
Title: YU-GI-OH! R, VOL. 3
Author: Kazuki Takahashi and Akira Ito
Contributor: by Kazuki Takahashi and Akira Ito

Description: Two brothers harmed in a ritual that was half magic/half science seek the legendary Philosopher’s Stone to make things right. But others seek the weapon of alchemy for their own nefarious means.
Title: FULLMETAL ALCHEMIST, VOL. 22
Author: Hiromu Arakawa

Description: The village of Hinamizawa is filled with many mysteries, but Keiichi Maebara must combat something closer to home: his friend is being abused by her uncle and no one seems to want to help.
Title: HIGURASHI: WHEN THEY CRY, VOL. 2
Author: Ryukishi07 and Jiro Suzuki
